emperature changes and other disruption of the earth's climate. Land use changes and forestry also play a role by altering the amount of greenhouse gases captured or released by carbon sinks\n\t","wordTheme":"OECD-Light Blue (Default)","lastUpdated":"","pubdate":"2023-01-04","banner":"","contentType":"","pdf":null,"pdfMediaHub":null,"pdfExternal":null,"content":[{"type":"chaptertitle","id":"heading-d1e77","content":[{"value":"Reader’s guide"}]},{"type":"paragraph","id":"p-d1e79","align":"justify","content":[{"value":"This report presents a digest of selected environmental trends in LAC countries in the areas of climate change, air quality and biodiversity. The analysis and key messages are based on indicators from the OECD Core Set of Environmental Indicators – a tool to monitor environmental progress and performance and to track the course towards sustainable development. It builds on the interactive Environment at a Glance web-based platform."}]},{"type":"paragraph","id":"p-d1e82","align":"justify","content":[{"value":"[Box on EAG platform]"}]},{"type":"section","id":"section-d1e85","content":[{"type":"section","id":"section-d1e86","content":[{"type":"sectiontitle2","id":"heading-d1e87","content":[{"value":"Comparability and interpretation"}]},{"type":"paragraph","id":"p-d1e98","align":"justify","content":[{"value":"The indicators used in this report are of varying relevance for different countries. Care should be taken when interpreting the indicators and when making international comparisons: "}]},{"type":"randlist","id":"d1e266","content":[{"type":"randlistitem","id":"d1e267","label":"","content":[{"type":"paragraph","id":"p-d1e102","content":[{"value":"National averages can mask significant variations within countries. l Definitions and measurement methods vary among countries, hence inter-country comparisons may not compare the same things."}]}]},{"type":"randlistitem","id":"d1e270","label":"","content":[{"type":"paragraph","id":"p-d1e107","content":[{"valu